TEXT -1192 56 Left 2 !.include tsmc018.lib
TEXT -1184 216 Left 2 ;.op
TEXT -1656 512 Left 2 !;.step temp -40 125 5
TEXT -2584 440 Left 2 ;TEMP COEFFICIENT\n \nWhen you run this .step temp -40 125 5 command, you can see how Vref\nchanges wrt temperature, here in this design Vref is at 1.1529 V at \n-40 degrees and 1.1512 V at 125 degrees, therefore over a 165 degree\ntemperature sweep, the change in voltage is about only 1.72mV.\nIn this design its about 10.42 ppm/ degree C
TEXT -2584 856 Left 2 ;LINE REGULATION\n \nThe Vref starts with 1.139V at V1=2V and goes up till 1.165V at V1=3V\nTherefore the difference is about 25.879mV over a 1 V , which is about \n25.88mV/V which is decent but not great\n \nCommand: .dc V1 1.2 3 0.01
TEXT -1640 976 Left 2 !;.dc V1 1.2 3 0.01
TEXT -2584 1216 Left 2 ;Worst-case startup (degenerate/zerocurrent state)\n \nCommand: .ic V(N004)=0 V(N006)=0 V(N005)=0 V(N008)=0\n.tran 200u\nV1 Vdd 0 PWL(0 0 5u 2.5 200u 2.5)\n \n \nVref starts at 0 and at 5us it gets stable to about 1.15V the V(n004)\nalso starts at 0 and gets stable to about 1.4V at around 6us and V(n006)\nalso starts at 0 and gets stable to about 1.32 V at around 4us. Therefore\nthe startup circuit is working as intended.
TEXT -1736 1264 Left 2 !;.ic V(N004)=0 V(N006)=0 V(N005)=0 V(N008)=0\n;.tran 200u
TEXT -2608 1736 Left 2 ;Normal-ramp startup\n \nCommand: V1 Vdd 0 PWL(0 0 1m 2.5)\n.tran 1.2m\n \n \nSmooth monotonic rise to final Vref , no overshoot,no oscillation, \nno glitch as Vdd crosses the knee voltage from test #3.(2V)\n \nWorks as intended
TEXT -1744 1760 Left 2 !;.tran 1.2m
TEXT -3192 2088 Left 2 ;Power-cycling restartup\n \nCommand: V1 Vdd 0 PWL(0 0 5u 2.5 80u 2.5 85u 0 90u 0 95u 2.5 200u 2.5)\n.tran 200u\n \nThis command is to check whether Vref recovers cleanly after each Vdd dip, \nnot just the first power-up and there is no problem, the Vref \nrecovers when Vdd recovers\n \nWorks as intended
TEXT -2144 2176 Left 2 !;.tran 200u
TEXT -2616 2440 Left 2 ;Startup robustness across temp corners\n \nRun A (-40°C):\n.ic V(N004)=0 V(N006)=0\n.temp -40\n.tran 200u\n \n \nRun B (27°C):\n.ic V(N004)=0 V(N006)=0\n.temp 27\n.tran 200u\n \n \nRun C (125°C):\n.ic V(N004)=0 V(N006)=0\n.temp 125\n.tran 200u\n \n \nThis test is to see whether Vref settles in all the corner cases as well.\n \nIt does!
TEXT -1696 2632 Left 2 !;.ic V(N004)=0 V(N006)=0\n;.temp 125\n;.tran 200u
TEXT -2616 3312 Left 2 ;PSRR\n \nCommand: \nV1 Vdd 0 PWL(0 0 5u 2.5 80u 2.5) AC 1\n.ac dec 10 1 1e6
TEXT -1648 3432 Left 2 !.ac dec 10 1 1e6
